class Solution {
    public boolean hasAlternatingBits(int n) {
        
        int currentBit = 0;

        while(n>0){

            currentBit = n%2;
            n= n/2;
            if(currentBit == n%2){
                return false;
            }
        }

        return true;

    }
}


Second Approach - Calculate right shift of the original input and then do XOR from between the right shift of the original input and input, it should be euqal to 1

Third Approach - to extract bit value of an input - O(logn)
